As we prepare to come back to school virtually this quarter, we have partnered with Arlene's Cuisine to provide our students with Grab and Go Meals. Each student that participates will be provided with breakfast and lunch for the week, and pick ups will be on Mondays from 10-12 at the back of the prep building. We are asking our families to please fill out the attached survey, so we can make sure we have an approximate number of meals to order. We look forward to seeing everyone again soon!!

post_text:
Dear Imagine Groveport Grizzly Families -
Following the recent decision made by Columbus City Schools in conjunction with Columbus Public Health and Franklin County Public Health, Groveport Community School has re-evaluated our reopening plan. The positivity rates, case counts, and trend lines are not conducive to opening schools in a hybrid model. They are recommending a continuing trend of decreasing rates before blended learning takes place. In alignment with this guidance, we will be starting the 2020-2021 school year in a 100% remote learning model for at least the first quarter.

The hybrid model we have been preparing for will need to change. It is our hope that our students may experience face-to-face learning at some point throughout the 2020-2021 school year. This will be an ever-changing situation and we will strive to make the safest decisions for our students and their families with the guidance and data from the health department.

The hybrid model we have been preparing for will need to change. It is our hope that our students may experience face-to-face learning at some point throughout the 2020-2021 school year. Teachers change the lives of millions of children every day. Their immense work and impact moves us beyond words! And with the abrupt end to the physical school year, our teachers have done even more to continue education with virtual classrooms and learning at home lessons... all to ensure every student has the tools they need to reach their full potential.

So, let’s all shower teachers in appreciation and share how we love (❤️) like (👍), celebrate (🎉) and care for (😍) our teachers!

post_text:
Governor Mike DeWine announced on Monday, 4/20/2020 the extension of the closure of Ohio school buildings due to the coronavirus pandemic through the remainder of the school year. This means our Distance Learning will continue!

We can’t thank all of our wonderful parents, staff, and students enough for your support as we quickly and successfully transitioned into distance learning. We couldn’t have done it without you! We ask for your flexibility, understanding and support as we continue to navigate in these difficult times.

We know that you are all very anxious about what the rest of the school year holds for our students, for events that had been planned, details about grading and more. Our leadership team is meeting and working on these details and there will be more information to come!

Please know that we miss our students and that they continue to be in our thoughts! Please check social media, DOJO, Google Classroom, and our website for the latest information. Thank you for your patience in allowing us to finalize the details as we respond to this unprecedented situation.

Imagine Groveport Families - as you may have heard, Governor DeWine has extended the school closure until Friday, May 1st. We wanted to let you know that our school is working on extended distance learning plans for all of our students. You will be hearing from your child's teacher about the new plans later this week.
It is very important that you communicate with your child's teacher via email or Dojo so that your child will be able to get their school work. You will be getting check in phone calls and Dojo messages from your child's teachers often throughout the week.
We will be posting weekly messages through this Facebook page, All Calls, our web page and Class Dojo.
You may still call the school if you have questions. The Elementary number is 614-574-4100 and the Prep number is 614-574-0037. We are answering the phones from 9-4 M-F to help you out with any questions or concerns you may have.

We miss you and can't wait to see all of our students!

post_text: A big thank you to the staff of Imagine Prep. They donated a lot of their time and artistic talents to decorate the entire building with candy creations. This year the staff voted on a Willy Wonka and the Chocolate Factory Theme. The building has a two story chocolate waterfall, a Chocolate River the entire length of the hallway, and a replica of the dragon boat. They even got the students involved by having them fill in empty spaces with their own candy designs. The building looks scrumptious! Way to go!

It's that time of year again- re-enrollment is upon us!

All students in grades kindergarten - 7th grade should have received a letter along with a re-enrollment form. To guarantee your student(s) a space for next year, you must return the completed re-enrollment form along with an updated lease or gas or electric bill.

If you have any questions concerning re-enrollment, please contact the office.
